Sean Crawford is a New Zealand artist who uses dead animals in his sculptures . 
  He has three animal sculptures on display at the Traffic Jam Gallery in Sydney . 
  The former plumber has been commissioned to build the Cloak of Remembrance for Anzac Day in Washington . 
  Mr Crawford said his interest in taxidermy started on his family farm . 
  He uses animal parts that have been killed for meat or pest control . 
  He said he has come under fire for 'manipulating the animal'